# AMIT1014 â€“ Web-Based Integrated Systems  
## Answers

---

## Question 1

### a) Differences between HTTP and HTTPS

HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol) and HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure) differ in several ways:

1. HTTP transfers data in plain text, while HTTPS encrypts data using SSL/TLS.
2. HTTP is not secure, whereas HTTPS provides secure communication.
3. HTTP does not verify website identity, while HTTPS uses digital certificates.
4. HTTP data can be intercepted or modified, while HTTPS ensures data integrity.
5. HTTP uses port 80, whereas HTTPS uses port 443.

---

### b) Concepts

#### (i) Web Server  
A web server is a system that stores, processes, and delivers web pages to clients over the Internet using HTTP or HTTPS.  
Example: Apache Web Server, Nginx.

#### (ii) Web Client  
A web client is an application that requests and displays web content from a web server.  
Example: Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox.

---

### c) Static Web Pages  
Static web pages are pages whose content does not change dynamically and are delivered to users exactly as stored on the server without server-side processing.

---

### d) Server-side Dynamic Pages

When a user requests a server-side dynamic page, the browser sends an HTTP request to the web server.  
The web server executes a server-side script such as PHP.  
The script may retrieve data from a database.  
After processing, HTML is dynamically generated and returned to the browser.

---

